Create Task

To create a Task:

  1. Select the New button
  2. Select the context you want the Task to be created

    Note: You can create the Task in the context of a cultural object or in the context of Folder or any system object. Creating Task in the context of another system objects means that this Task will be part of that context and the permissions on that Task will depend on this context.

     

  3. Select "Task" from the drop-down with types.
     

    Note: To find easily "Task" in the list with system objects that can be created you can start to type directly in the field. The list with types is filtered as you write in the field.

     

  4. Fill Task assignment section fields.
  5. Choose a Template
  6. Press Create or Open depending on whether you prefer to open the the task and continue to edit it or just quick to create it.
